				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I used to get so frustrated when soloing over a one chord groove. I just kept running out of ideas! It was when I was transcribing a bass solo of Jeff Berlin's that I discovered a super cool way of using the same information I already new, and simply moving the shapes into different keys - thereby getting a whole new sound and flavor over one chord... without having to do too many brain gymnastics! :)</p>
<p>In this bass lesson I'm going to let you in on what I learned and exactly how you can use it in your playing!</p>
<p>Scott :)<br />
